## Minimal local setup of gin repo with a gin-auth user store

- create repo server root folder and `repos/git` and `users` folder e.g.
    mkdir repodata
    mkdir repodata/repos
    mkdir repodata/repos/git
    mkdir repodata/users
- create file `user.store` at the root of the repo directory and
    add `ginauth@[gin-auth url]` (url of the auth server) to the file. e.g.
    cd repodata
    echo "ginauth@http://localhosts:8081" >> user.store
- start the repo server in the root of the repo directory
    gin-repod

## Set up dev environment of gin-repo with a gin-auth user store

- create repo server root folder e.g. `repodata` and change into it
- create file `user.store` at the root of the repo directory and
    add `ginauth@[gin-auth url]` (url of the auth server) to the file. e.g.
    cd repodata
    echo "ginauth@http://localhosts:8081" >> user.store
- run `mkdata.py` script with the provided `data.yml` file
  in the root of the directory to set up the test repo structure.
    python [gin-repo-path]/contrib/mkdata.py [gin-repo-path]/contrib/data.yml
- start the repo server in the root of the repo directory
